 takes his time, smoothing back a stray lock of unreliably dark hair, and sighs. He turns to his assistant, Nan Wilder, and raises his eyebrows. Nan shrugs in response.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.5in;line-height:150%">
<span style="font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Palatino Linotype&quot;,serif; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Taft speaks directly to a meek-looking man at the table. “Flying, Bailey, really?”</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:.5in;line-height:150%">
